alert.note: Alert for Western Aleutians (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 27 at 3:07PM AKST until January 29 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM NOON SATURDAY TO NOON AKST SUNDAY... * WHAT...South winds 50 to 65 mph with gusts up to 75 mph expected. * WHERE...Western Aleutians. * WHEN...From noon Saturday to noon AKST Sunday. * IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property, * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A period of strong east to southeasterly winds will accompany a deep North Pacific low as its front pushes across the western Aleutians Saturday afternoon through Sunday morning. Gusts up to 75 mph remain forecast, though expect winds to diminish somewhat Saturday evening as southerly winds along the front shift to southwesterly on the south side of the passing low through early Sunday morning.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind.
